      <body>
         <!-- please fill out the template below, replacing text in square brackets with the actual information -->
         <head>
            <title> CHARLOTTE WHITNEY</title>
            <date>Statement taken ll-28-25</date>
            <orgName> Secretary to Mrs. Shelby</orgName>
         </head>
         <div>
            <byline><persName ref="Quinn">Meghan Quinn</persName></byline>
            <!-- make sure to add your unique identifier from the header, by adding the @ref attribute in the byline element -->

            <!-- Paste your transcription into the structure below, repeating the pattern for each question and answer. -->

            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker>WHITNEY:</speaker>
               <ab>** and <persName ref="#minter_mary">Mary</persName> stood up and looked at her
                     <persName ref="#shelby_charlotte">mother</persName> and said, <quote>"Do you
                     really mean that?"</quote> and Mrs. Shelby said, <quote>"I certainly
                     do."</quote> She accused her of being intimate with <persName ref="#taylor_william"
                     >Taylor</persName>and then made other remarks. ** <persName ref="#minter_mary"
                     >She</persName> locked herself in her <placeName> mother's room </placeName>**
                  and she got the <objectName type="weapon">gun</objectName> and tried to kill
                  herself, but there was a safety catch on it and it wouldn't go off. ** <persName
                     ref="#minter_mary">Mary</persName> was monkeying with this thing and finally the
                  catch released itself and the darn <objectName type="weapon">gun</objectName> went
                  off. **</ab>
            </sp>

            <sp select="question">
               <speaker>POLICE:</speaker>
               <ab>What kind of a <objectName type="weapon">gun</objectName> was that?</ab>
            </sp>

            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker>WHITNEY:</speaker>
               <ab>
                  <objectName type="weapon">Revolver</objectName>. A little snub-nosed thing.</ab>
            </sp>

            <sp select="question">
               <speaker>POLICE:</speaker>
               <ab>Was it a black one?</ab>
            </sp>


            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker>WHITNEY:</speaker>
               <ab>Yes.</ab>
            </sp>

            <sp select="question">
               <speaker>POLICE:</speaker>
               <ab>Who did the <objectName type="weapon">gun</objectName> belong to?</ab>
            </sp>

            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker>WHITNEY:</speaker>
               <ab><persName ref="#shelby_charlotte">Mrs. Shelby</persName>.</ab>
            </sp>

            <sp select="question">
               <speaker>POLICE: </speaker>
               <ab>Do you know how long <persName ref="#shelby_charlotte">she</persName> had it?</ab>
            </sp>

            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker>WHITNEY:</speaker>
               <ab>Oh, she always carried a <objectName type="weapon">gun</objectName>. I mean we
                  always kept one in the <placeName>house</placeName>.</ab>
            </sp>


            <sp select="question">
               <speaker>POLICE:</speaker>
               <ab><persName ref="#shelby_charlotte">She</persName> knew how to handle a <objectName
                     type="weapon">gun</objectName>?</ab>
            </sp>

            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker>WHITNEY:</speaker>
               <ab>Oh, I should say so. ** <time>one night</time> when we (witness and Mrs. Shelby)
                  went down to <placeName>Taylor's</placeName> after <persName ref="#minter_mary">Mary
                  </persName>, <persName ref="#shelby_charlotte">Mrs. Shelby</persName> took the <objectName
                     type="weapon">gun</objectName>, but I don't think <persName ref="#shelby_charlotte"
                     >she</persName> had any intention of using it on <persName ref="#minter_mary"
                     >Mary</persName>.</ab>
            </sp>

            <sp select="question">
               <speaker>POLICE:</speaker>
               <ab>Did <persName ref="#shelby_charlotte">she</persName> (Shelby) threaten to kill <persName ref="#taylor_william">him</persName> (Taylor)?</ab>
            </sp>

            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker>WHITNEY:</speaker>
               <ab>Yes. Several people heard that. It was in <placeName>my office</placeName>.</ab>
            </sp>

            <sp select="question">
               <speaker>POLICE:</speaker>
               <ab>When was <objectName type="weapon">it</objectName> in your office?</ab>
            </sp>

            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker>WHITNEY:</speaker>
               <ab>That was in <time>1920</time>, in the summer. He (Taylor) had finished directing
                  with <persName ref="#minter_mary">Mary</persName>. <persName ref="#maigne_charles">Charley Maigne</persName>
                  was directing her and Charley was in the <placeName>office</placeName>, and
                     <persName ref="#taylor_william">Taylor</persName> was in the office. **</ab>
            </sp>

            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker>WHITNEY:</speaker>
               <ab>** She said, <quote>"If I ever catch you hanging around Mary again, I will blow
                     your god damned brains out."</quote>
                  <persName ref="#maigne_charles">She</persName> walked right up to <persName ref="#taylor_william"
                     >him</persName>. She was just livid with rage and shook her <objectName
                     type="body_part">fist</objectName> in his <objectName type="body_part"
                     >face</objectName> and swore dozens of times.</ab>
            </sp>

            <sp select="question">
               <speaker>POLICE:</speaker>
               <ab>Do you know of an incident that occurred in which <persName ref="#blue_monte">Monte
                     Blue</persName> was supposed to have been run out of the <placeName>dressing
                     room</placeName> with a <objectName type="weapon">gun</objectName> by <persName
                     ref="#shelby_charlotte">Mrs. Shelby</persName>?</ab>
            </sp>

            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker>WHITNEY:</speaker>
               <ab>Well, I don't know that <persName ref="#shelby_charlotte">she</persName> had a <objectName
                     type="weapon">gun</objectName>, but I know that he was run out of the
                     <placeName>dressing room</placeName>, because he ran into my
                     <placeName>office</placeName> from the dressing room. (Referring to incidents
                  surrounding visit of Mrs. Shelby to Taylor's residence in search of Mary) ** She
                  (Mrs. Shelby) said, <quote>"I will take my gun, and if I find her there I am going
                     to kill her."</quote> I begged her not to take it ** She wouldn't do it, so she
                  went with the <objectName type="weapon">gun.</objectName> **</ab>
            </sp>

            <sp select="question">
               <speaker>POLICE:</speaker>
               <ab>She had the <objectName type="weapon">gun</objectName> with her at that
                  time?</ab>
            </sp>

            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker>WHITNEY:</speaker>
               <ab>She had it in her <objectName type="body_part">hand</objectName> and her
                     <objectName type="clothing">coat sleeve</objectName>; she had big coat sleeves
                  and the <objectName type="weapon">gun</objectName> was in her <objectName
                     type="body_part">hand</objectName> hid by her coat sleeve.</ab>
            </sp>

            <sp select="question">
               <speaker>POLICE:</speaker>
               <ab>Do you know of any other trouble with <persName ref="#taylor_william">Taylor</persName>
                  that <persName ref="#shelby_charlotte">Mrs. Shelby</persName> had?</ab>
            </sp>

            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker>WHITNEY:</speaker>
               <ab>They fought all the time. Always on the <placeName>set</placeName> when he was
                  directing.</ab>
            </sp>

            <sp select="question">
               <speaker>POLICE:</speaker>
               <ab>Was the situation getting worse a11 the time?</ab>
            </sp>

            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker>WHITNEY:</speaker>
               <ab>A11 the time. It was terrible.</ab>
            </sp>

            <sp select="question">
               <speaker>POLICE:</speaker>
               <ab>Was there anyone else present at any of these battles, that you recall, over
                     <persName ref="#taylor_william">Mr. Taylor</persName>?</ab>
            </sp>

            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker>WHITNEY:</speaker>
               <ab>Well, <persName ref="#stockdale_carl">Earl Stockdale</persName>. I am sure he was
                  present.</ab>
            </sp>

            <sp select="question">
               <speaker>POLICE:</speaker>
               <ab>Do you know any of her servants (Shelby's) at the time of the murder?</ab>
            </sp>

            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker>WHITNEY:</speaker>
               <ab>I knew them only by their first names. ** We had a butler named <persName
                     ref="Frederick">Frederick</persName>., a butler named ­<persName ref="Ernest"
                     >Ernest</persName>, and a cook named <persName ref="Pauline"
                  >Pauline</persName>. <persName ref="Stewart">Edith Stewart</persName> was
                     <persName ref="#minter_mary">Mary's</persName> personal maid at that time</ab>
            </sp>

            <sp select="question">
               <speaker>POLICE:</speaker>
               <ab>Can you think of any friends of yours, or any acquaintances of <persName
                     ref="#shelby_charlotte">Shelby</persName>, in any way at all, that were associating with
                  or closely associated with them immediately prior to, or immediately after,
                     <persName ref="#taylor_william">Taylor's</persName> murder?</ab>
            </sp>

            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker>WHITNEY:</speaker>
               <ab>
                  <persName ref="#periolet_george">M. George Periolet.</persName></ab>
            </sp>

            <sp select="question">
               <speaker>WHITNEY:</speaker>
               <ab>He is at <placeName>Engstrom Apartments, Los Angeles.</placeName> ** Have you
                  talked to <persName ref="#mcpherson_jeanne">Jeanne McPherson</persName> at all? <persName ref="#mcpherson_jeanne">Jeanne</persName>
                  knows a great, big, large lot. ** <persName ref="#mcpherson_jeanne">Jeanne</persName> came over to see <persName ref="#minter_mary"
                     >Mary</persName> a day or so after the murder. She would be a good person for
                  you to talk to. And her mother , <persName ref="#oneil">Mrs.
                  O'Neil</persName>.</ab>
            </sp>

            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker>POLICE:</speaker>
               <ab>Well, going back to that old subject of the <objectName type="weapon"
                     >gun</objectName>, I just wanted to be sure that <persName ref="#shelby_charlotte">Mrs.
                     Shelby</persName> had it in the <placeName>house</placeName> for a long
                  time.</ab>
            </sp>

            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker>WHITNEY:</speaker>
               <ab>Oh yes, there was always a <objectName type="weapon">gun</objectName>.</ab>
            </sp>

            <sp select="question">
               <speaker>POLICE:</speaker>
               <ab>If anybody said that <persName ref="#shelby_charlotte">Mrs. She1by</persName> did not know
                  anything about a <objectName type="weapon">pistol or revolver</objectName>, and
                  was afraid of one, that would not be true?</ab>
            </sp>

            <sp select="answer">
               <speaker>WHITNEY:</speaker>
               <ab>That's ridiculous. <persName ref="#shelby_charlotte">Mrs. Shelby</persName> was not afraid
                  of anything.</ab>
            </sp>
         </div>
